    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1952-01-31T11:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1952-01-31T11:00:00-05:00" n="313"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d313">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.5/1–3152: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="#p_GIFFORDWS1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gifford</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Department of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d313fn1">Repeated for information to Paris and Bonn.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">priority</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1952-01-31T16:00:00+00:00"
                            >January 31, 1952—4 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>3288. <gloss target="#t_FonOff1">FonOff</gloss> advises <persName
                        corresp="#p_BLANKENHORNHAH1">Blankenhorn</persName> “showed up in London
                    last week” ostensibly on private business, but called “informally” on <persName
                        corresp="#p_ROBERTSSFK1">Frank Roberts</persName>, Dep Under Secy in charge
                    of Ger Affairs. Stated that <persName corresp="#p_ADENAUERK1"
                        >Adenauer</persName> hoped Brit wld appreciate serious Parl difficulties
                    impending in Bonn and referred in gen terms to security controls, fin
                    contribution and constitution of restitution court, without making any specific
                    requests. Then went on to say that <persName corresp="#p_HALLSTEINW1"
                        >Hallstein</persName> wld be making a statement in Paris at <gloss
                        target="#t_EDC1">EDC</gloss>
                    <gloss target="#t_FonMin1">FonMin</gloss> mtg and wld raise question Ger-<gloss
                        target="#t_NATO1">NATO</gloss> membership.<note n="2" xml:id="d313fn2"
                        >Regarding the Six-Power Meetings of Foreign Ministers at Paris, Jan. 26–27
                        under reference here, see the editorial note, <ref target="#pg_594">p.
                            594</ref>.</note> He indicated belief <persName corresp="#p_ADENAUERK1"
                        >Adenauer</persName> Parl problems might be adequately met if <gloss
                        target="#t_EDC1">EDC</gloss> cld have “corporate membership” in <gloss
                        target="#t_NATO1">NATO</gloss> since fully realized question Ger membership
                    cld be solved only gradually and not in time to meet <persName
                        corresp="#p_ADENAUERK1">Adenauer</persName> Parl problems.</p>
                <p>In response to question from <persName corresp="#p_ROBERTSSFK1"
                        >Roberts</persName>, <persName corresp="#p_BLANKENHORNHAH1"
                        >Blankenhorn</persName> stated that if some such arrangement were possible,
                    Gers wld not press question their national membership and agreed that national
                    membership in <pb facs="0652" n="608" xml:id="pg_608"/>
                    <gloss target="#t_NATO1">NATO</gloss> of other <gloss target="#t_EDC1"
                        >EDC</gloss> participants wld continue. <gloss target="#t_FonOff1"
                        >FonOff</gloss> rep stated that after further consideration <persName
                        corresp="#p_BLANKENHORNHAH1">Blankenhorn</persName> statement doubt he meant
                    “membership” for <gloss target="#t_EDC1">EDC</gloss> in literal sense since
                        <gloss target="#t_FonOff1">FonOff</gloss> legal advisors consider this
                    precluded by terms of <gloss target="#t_NATO1">NATO</gloss> agrmt. <gloss
                        target="#t_FonOff1">FonOff</gloss> believes he actually meant <gloss
                        target="#t_EDC1">EDC</gloss> representation on appropriate <gloss
                        target="#t_NATO1">NATO</gloss> bodies. If this Ger position, <gloss
                        target="#t_FonOff1">FonOff</gloss> think question whether Ger believe <gloss
                        target="#t_NATO1">NAT</gloss> representation other <gloss target="#t_EDC1"
                        >EDC</gloss> participants in such bodies shld continue wld then become
                    relevant.</p>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_FonOff1">FonOff</gloss> has noted discrepancy between
                        <persName corresp="#p_BLANKENHORNHAH1">Blankenhorn</persName>’s statement
                    and that of <persName corresp="#p_HALLSTEINW1">Hallstein</persName> to effect
                    other <gloss target="#t_EDC1">EDC</gloss> participants shld renounce <gloss
                        target="#t_NATO1">NATO</gloss> membership in favor corporate <gloss
                        target="#t_EDC1">EDC</gloss> membership and believes <persName
                        corresp="#p_HALLSTEINW1">Hallstein</persName>’s statement represents initial
                    bargaining proposal and <persName corresp="#p_BLANKENHORNHAH1"
                        >Blankenhorn</persName>’s represents position to which <gloss
                        target="#t_FedRep1">FedRep</gloss> willing to be driven back.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_GIFFORDWS1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Gifford</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
